<seg id="82">VIES system</seg>
<seg id="83">In order to monitor the application of the right to VAT exemption on intra-Community supplies of goods, a VAT information exchange system has been set up within the EU.</seg>
<seg id="84">It includes the VIES electronic system, which allows the tax authorities of the EU Member States to check whether the supplier was entitled to exempt the taxable supply from VAT and, conversely, whether the purchaser duly declared and taxed the acquired goods.</seg>
<seg id="85">The VIES information system is not centralised within the EU.</seg>
<seg id="86">Each Member State is developing its own VIES system.</seg>
<seg id="87">National systems operate on a common principle and are interconnected through the EU's common communication network, the so-called CCN (Common Communication Network; see diagram below).</seg>
<seg id="88">In the Czech Republic, the VIES system was connected to the automated tax information system (hereinafter referred to as "ADIS") and in Slovakia to the application software of the tax information system (hereinafter referred to as "APV DIS").</seg>
<seg id="89">These systems are used by the tax or tax authorities as technical support for executive and management activities in the administration of taxes and duties.</seg>
<seg id="90">International administrative cooperation</seg>
<seg id="91">Through international administrative cooperation, the tax administration of each EU Member State obtains information on tax subjects that it would not have been able to obtain on its own without such cooperation.</seg>
<seg id="92">The main objective of international administrative cooperation is the fight against tax evasion and tax losses.</seg>
<seg id="93">According to Council Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003, each Member State shall establish a central unit within the internal organisational structure in the field of administrative cooperation between EU Member States in the administration of VAT, the so-called "central unit." CLO (Central Liaison Office).</seg>
<seg id="94">In the Czech Republic, the tasks arising from international cooperation are performed by the Ministry of Finance - the Central Financial and Tax Directorate, where the Department of International Cooperation in the Administration of VAT (hereinafter referred to as MF CLO) was established.</seg>
<seg id="95">The function of the CLO in the Slovak Republic is performed by the Tax Directorate of the Slovak Republic, Department of International Administrative Cooperation (hereinafter referred to as "DR CLO").</seg>
<seg id="96">These departments, among other things, communicate with EU foreign administrations in particular in the field of information exchange within the VIES system, exchange of spontaneous information and information at the request of EU tax administrations, coordination of multilateral (simultaneous) tax controls, verification of tax identification numbers (hereinafter referred to as VAT numbers) of persons registered for VAT in other EU Member States and communication with the European Commission.</seg>
<seg id="97">In order to examine a certain intra-Community transaction or to obtain other information relating to a particular tax entity, the tax authorities send requests for information to the EU through the MF CLO or DR CLO.</seg>
<seg id="98">Through these requests, they obtain information from the requested Member States which they can use to determine VAT correctly.</seg>
<seg id="99">Requests for information are sent mostly in electronic form between the Customs of the EU Member States, using a standardised SCAC form.</seg>
