<seg id="226">6.2 Deficiencies identified</seg>
<seg id="227">The results of the audit in the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic pointed to some similar shortcomings that did not have a major impact on the management of state funds and property.</seg>
<seg id="228">These shortcomings were mainly in the following areas: a) the use of state budget funds contrary to the purpose for which they were designated by the Act on the State Budget, when current expenditures were used to cover actions in the nature of technical appreciation of fixed tangible assets; b) the violation of the Act on Accounting in the area of inventories and non-compliance with the guiding chart of accounts.</seg>
