<p>
<seg id="1">Report on the Outcome of International Cooperation in Excise Duty Administration Inspections between the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic in 2006</seg>
<seg id="2">Introductory word</seg>
<seg id="3">The submitted joint report informs on the course and outcome of international cooperation in parallel audits carried out by the Supreme Audit Office, the Czech Republic and the Supreme Audit Office of the Slovak Republic, focused on the administration of excise duties in the period after the accession of both countries to the European Union.</seg>
<seg id="4">The cooperation was implemented on the basis of a control cooperation contract concluded in February 2006.</seg>
<seg id="5">The topic of parallel controls was chosen with regard to a fundamental change in the system of collecting excise duties, which occurred in connection with the integration of the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic into the internal market of the European Union as of 1 May 2004.</seg>
<seg id="6">The functioning of the internal market of the European Union requires the free movement of goods, including excise goods.</seg>
<seg id="7">The basic principle is to allow goods free of tax to circulate until the date of their delivery for final consumption.</seg>
<seg id="8">In accordance with that principle, the new legislation adopted in both countries allows the movement of goods under fiscal supervision under a duty suspension arrangement.</seg>
